msgid ""
"Klein for Ray API stability, compatibility, deprecation, and public-"
"contract policy."
msgstr "Klein for Ray API 稳定性、兼容性、弃用及公共契约政策。"

msgid "API stability and compatibility"
msgstr "API 稳定性与兼容性"

msgid ""
"Klein for Ray is an alpha project. The word **public** identifies an "
"intended application or extension boundary; it does not yet mean the 1.0 "
"compatibility guarantee of a mature stable release. Pin the Klein and Ray"
" versions used in production and read [CHANGELOG.md](https://github.com"
"/yuchen-ecnu/klein/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md) before upgrading."
msgstr "Klein for Ray 目前处于 alpha 阶段。**公共（public）** 表示预期供应用程序或扩展使用的边界，但尚不代表成熟稳定版所提供的 1.0 兼容性保证。请固定生产环境使用的 Klein 和 Ray 版本，并在升级前阅读 [CHANGELOG.md](https://github.com/yuchen-ecnu/klein/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md)。"

msgid "Contract categories"
msgstr "契约类别"

msgid "Category"
msgstr "类别"

msgid "How to recognize it"
msgstr "识别方式"

msgid "Current promise"
msgstr "当前承诺"

msgid "Documented application API"
msgstr "有文档说明的应用 API"

msgid ""
"Listed in the [API reference](api/api.rst), connector catalog, CLI "
"reference, or configuration reference"
msgstr "列在 [API 参考](api/api.rst)、连接器目录、CLI 参考或配置参考中"

msgid ""
"Supported for the documented release. Alpha changes are announced in the "
"changelog and upgrade guide."
msgstr "在相应文档版本中受支持。alpha 阶段的变更会在变更日志和升级指南中公布。"

msgid "Documented extension API"
msgstr "有文档说明的扩展 API"

msgid ""
"Custom source/sink, table factory, partitioner, state backend, metric, "
"and related contracts explicitly described in the reference"
msgstr "参考文档中明确说明的自定义源/接收器、表工厂、分区器、状态后端、指标及相关契约"

msgid ""
"Intended for integrations, but more likely to evolve before 1.0. Pin the "
"exact release and test lifecycle behavior."
msgstr "供集成使用，但在 1.0 之前更可能发生演进。请固定确切版本并测试生命周期行为。"

msgid "Delegated Ray API"
msgstr "委托给 Ray 的 API"

msgid "Dynamic `ray.klein.read_*` and `stream.data.*` methods"
msgstr "动态 `ray.klein.read_*` 和 `stream.data.*` 方法"

msgid ""
"Signature, schema, and batch behavior belong to the pinned Ray release. "
"Klein only promises the documented adapter boundary."
msgstr "签名、模式和批处理行为由固定的 Ray 版本定义。Klein 仅保证文档所述的适配器边界。"

msgid "Operational contract"
msgstr "运维契约"

msgid ""
"Configuration keys, CLI syntax, JSON snapshots, metric names/labels, "
"checkpoint layout, and environment variables"
msgstr "配置键、CLI 语法、JSON 快照、指标名称/标签、检查点布局和环境变量"

msgid ""
"Public only where explicitly documented. Consumers must tolerate additive"
" JSON fields. Alpha releases can make announced breaking changes."
msgstr "仅明确写入文档的部分属于公共契约。使用方必须能容忍新增 JSON 字段。alpha 版本可以进行已公布的破坏性变更。"

msgid "Internal implementation"
msgstr "内部实现"

msgid ""
"`ray.klein._internal`, most of `ray.klein.runtime`, underscore-prefixed "
"names, undocumented actor methods, and undocumented files"
msgstr "`ray.klein._internal`、`ray.klein.runtime` 的大部分内容、以下划线开头的名称、未记录的 actor 方法和未记录的文件"

msgid ""
"No compatibility promise. Do not import or automate against these "
"surfaces."
msgstr "不提供兼容性承诺。请勿导入这些接口，也不要针对它们编写自动化。"

msgid ""
"An object appearing in Python's `dir()` or a package `__all__` is not by "
"itself a stability declaration. The documentation is the source of truth."
" Some runtime bridge names remain top-level for the bundled CLI; the "
"[top-level namespace reference](api/top_level.rst) identifies them as "
"non-application APIs."
msgstr "某个对象出现在 Python 的 `dir()` 或包的 `__all__` 中，本身并不代表稳定性声明。文档才是事实依据。为支持随附的 CLI，一些运行时桥接名称仍保留在顶层；[顶层命名空间参考](api/top_level.rst) 会将它们标明为非应用 API。"

msgid "What compatibility means"
msgstr "兼容性的含义"

msgid "Compatibility has several independent dimensions:"
msgstr "兼容性包含多个相互独立的维度："

msgid "Python source compatibility"
msgstr "Python 源码兼容性"

msgid ""
"Existing documented calls continue to import and accept the same "
"arguments."
msgstr "现有且有文档说明的调用仍可导入，并接受相同的参数。"

msgid "Behavioral compatibility"
msgstr "行为兼容性"

msgid ""
"Ordering, state, delivery, execution-mode, and failure semantics remain "
"the same. A source-compatible change can still be behaviorally "
"incompatible."
msgstr "顺序、状态、交付、执行模式和故障语义保持不变。源码兼容的变更仍可能在行为上不兼容。"

msgid "Operational compatibility"
msgstr "运维兼容性"

msgid ""
"Automation can continue to use documented configuration, CLI, snapshot, "
"and metric contracts. New JSON fields and new enum values can be added; "
"clients must ignore fields they do not understand."
msgstr "自动化可以继续使用有文档说明的配置、CLI、快照和指标契约。可以新增 JSON 字段和枚举值；客户端必须忽略无法识别的字段。"

msgid "State compatibility"
msgstr "状态兼容性"

msgid ""
"A new deployment can read checkpoint metadata, source positions, managed "
"state, timers, and sink committables written by the old deployment. This "
"is not guaranteed across arbitrary alpha versions."
msgstr "新部署可以读取旧部署写入的检查点元数据、源位置、托管状态、定时器和接收器可提交项。任意 alpha 版本之间并不保证这一点。"

msgid "Wire compatibility"
msgstr "线协议兼容性"

msgid ""
"Running tasks, actors, and drivers can exchange messages. Klein does not "
"support a rolling binary upgrade in which one live job mixes Klein "
"versions."
msgstr "运行中的任务、actor 和驱动程序可以交换消息。Klein 不支持在同一个运行中作业里混用不同 Klein 版本的滚动二进制升级。"

msgid "Dependency compatibility"
msgstr "依赖兼容性"

msgid ""
"The application, all eligible workers, connector clients, and Ray cluster"
" use versions in the tested matrix. See "
"[Compatibility](compatibility.md)."
msgstr "应用程序、所有符合条件的工作节点、连接器客户端和 Ray 集群均使用测试矩阵内的版本。请参阅[兼容性](compatibility.md)。"

msgid ""
"Do not infer state or wire compatibility from a successful import. Use "
"the procedure in [Upgrading](upgrading.md)."
msgstr "不要根据导入成功来推断状态或线协议兼容性。请遵循[升级](upgrading.md)中的流程。"

msgid "Public API rules"
msgstr "公共 API 规则"

msgid ""
"Application code should import ordinary graph contracts from `ray.klein`,"
" specialized contracts from `ray.klein.api`, configuration descriptors "
"from `ray.klein.config`, and managed-state contracts from "
"`ray.klein.state`."
msgstr "应用代码应从 `ray.klein` 导入常规图契约，从 `ray.klein.api` 导入专用契约，从 `ray.klein.config` 导入配置描述符，并从 `ray.klein.state` 导入托管状态契约。"

msgid ""
"`ray.klein.runtime.partitioning` is the documented exception for custom "
"partitioners. Other runtime modules are implementation details unless a "
"reference page says otherwise."
msgstr "`ray.klein.runtime.partitioning` 是供自定义分区器使用且有文档说明的例外。除非参考页面另有说明，否则其他运行时模块均属于实现细节。"

msgid ""
"A method, option, or connector is supported only in the execution modes "
"shown in the [operator compatibility matrix](operator-compatibility.md) "
"or connector catalog."
msgstr "方法、选项或连接器仅在[算子兼容性矩阵](operator-compatibility.md)或连接器目录所列的执行模式中受支持。"

msgid ""
"Optional integrations may raise `ModuleNotFoundError` until their named "
"package extra and native dependencies are installed on every worker."
msgstr "在每个工作节点上安装相应的可选依赖组和原生依赖之前，可选集成可能抛出 `ModuleNotFoundError`。"

msgid ""
"A callable's Python type annotation does not upgrade its runtime "
"contract. Record shape, batch format, serialization, and lifecycle rules "
"remain those in the programming guide."
msgstr "可调用对象的 Python 类型注解不会提升其运行时契约。记录形状、批格式、序列化和生命周期规则仍以编程指南为准。"

msgid "Dynamic Ray Data surface"
msgstr "动态 Ray Data 接口面"

msgid ""
"Klein discovers public Ray Data readers and Dataset methods from the "
"installed compatible Ray version. This avoids copying a large, version-"
"sensitive API, but it means the names are not all present in "
"`ray.klein.__all__` or static API pages."
msgstr "Klein 从已安装的兼容 Ray 版本中发现公共 Ray Data 读取器和 Dataset 方法。这样无需复制庞大且对版本敏感的 API，但也意味着这些名称不会全部出现在 `ray.klein.__all__` 或静态 API 页面中。"

msgid "Use:"
msgstr "用法："

msgid ""
"Library code that supports several Ray patches should check availability "
"rather than assume a method exists. Native `DataStream` methods retain "
"Klein semantics; dynamic methods retain Ray Data semantics and are batch-"
"only unless the [interop guide](ray-data-interop.md) explicitly documents"
" a streaming form."
msgstr "支持多个 Ray 补丁版本的库代码应检查功能是否可用，而不要假定某个方法一定存在。原生 `DataStream` 方法保留 Klein 语义；动态方法保留 Ray Data 语义，并且仅支持批处理，除非[互操作指南](ray-data-interop.md)明确记录了流处理形式。"

msgid "Deprecation policy before 1.0"
msgstr "1.0 之前的弃用政策"

msgid ""
"Klein has no fixed multi-release deprecation window while it is alpha. "
"The project follows this best-effort process for a documented contract:"
msgstr "Klein 在 alpha 阶段没有固定的跨版本弃用窗口。对于已有文档的契约，项目会尽力遵循以下流程："

msgid ""
"Record the old behavior, replacement, and compatibility impact in the "
"changelog and upgrade guide."
msgstr "在变更日志和升级指南中记录旧行为、替代方案及兼容性影响。"

msgid ""
"Emit a warning when a safe runtime warning is possible and does not "
"create excessive worker log volume."
msgstr "如果能够安全地发出运行时警告且不会产生过量工作节点日志，则发出警告。"

msgid ""
"Keep read compatibility for persisted state when practical, or state "
"clearly that a migration or clean start is required."
msgstr "在可行时保持对持久化状态的读取兼容性，否则明确说明需要迁移或全新启动。"

msgid "Add or update contract tests so the announced boundary is reviewable."
msgstr "新增或更新契约测试，使公布的边界可以接受审查。"

msgid ""
"Security fixes, correctness fixes, and dependency incompatibilities can "
"require an immediate change. Do not suppress deprecation or compatibility"
" warnings without reviewing the associated release note."
msgstr "安全修复、正确性修复和依赖不兼容可能要求立即变更。请勿在未审阅相关发布说明的情况下屏蔽弃用或兼容性警告。"

msgid "Contracts that require explicit review"
msgstr "需要明确审查的契约"

msgid ""
"Changes to any of the following need documentation, tests, and an upgrade"
" note:"
msgstr "对以下任何内容的变更都需要文档、测试和升级说明："

msgid "a top-level or documented extension API;"
msgstr "顶层 API 或有文档说明的扩展 API；"

msgid "operator ordering, partitioning, changelog, or delivery behavior;"
msgstr "算子顺序、分区、变更日志或交付行为；"

msgid "a configuration key, default, type, precedence, or environment spelling;"
msgstr "配置键、默认值、类型、优先级或环境变量拼写；"

msgid "a CLI command, exit behavior, or documented JSON field;"
msgstr "CLI 命令、退出行为或有文档说明的 JSON 字段；"

msgid "a metric name, kind, unit, label, or histogram boundary;"
msgstr "指标名称、种类、单位、标签或直方图区间边界；"

msgid ""
"checkpoint manifests, state codecs, key hashing, key groups, source "
"state, or sink committables;"
msgstr "检查点清单、状态编解码器、键哈希、键组、源状态或接收器可提交项；"

msgid "connector schema, offset ownership, transaction behavior, or option;"
msgstr "连接器模式、偏移量所有权、事务行为或选项；"

msgid "supported Python, Ray, SQLGlot, PyArrow, or connector dependency ranges."
msgstr "受支持的 Python、Ray、SQLGlot、PyArrow 或连接器依赖版本范围。"

msgid ""
"The [documentation contract tests](testing.md) mechanically cover part of"
" this surface. They complement, rather than replace, upgrade testing with"
" real production-shaped state."
msgstr "[文档契约测试](testing.md)以机械方式覆盖了其中一部分。它们是使用真实生产形态状态进行升级测试的补充，而非替代。"

msgid "Reporting an accidental break"
msgstr "报告意外破坏"

msgid "Open a reproducible issue with:"
msgstr "请提交可复现的问题，并包含："

msgid "old and new Klein, Ray, Python, and connector versions;"
msgstr "新旧 Klein、Ray、Python 和连接器版本；"

msgid ""
"whether the break concerns source, behavior, operations, or persisted "
"state;"
msgstr "破坏涉及源码、行为、运维还是持久化状态；"

msgid "the smallest graph and configuration that demonstrate it;"
msgstr "能够复现问题的最小图和配置；"

msgid ""
"the old checkpoint format/version and a copy of non-sensitive error "
"output;"
msgstr "旧检查点的格式/版本以及不含敏感信息的错误输出副本；"

msgid "whether a clean start works and whether rollback remains possible."
msgstr "全新启动是否可行，以及是否仍能回滚。"

msgid ""
"Use the private process in the project security policy when the break can"
" expose data, credentials, or code execution."
msgstr "如果该破坏可能暴露数据、凭据或代码执行能力，请使用项目安全政策规定的私密报告流程。"
